# Noblinks Lens — Pricing Strategy

---

## Core Pricing Principle

The value of Lens is not in reading the report — it is in the
decision confidence it creates. A company spending €15k/month on AWS
can justify €500/month for a tool that tells them whether migration
to Hetzner (saving €10k/month) will succeed or destroy their product.

Price to the value of the decision, not the cost of the API calls.

---

## Pricing Model: Tiered Subscription + Per-Analysis Credits

Rationale:
- Subscription anchors the product as a recurring tool, not a one-time report
- Credits give flexibility without a seat model (seats don't fit — it's one
  analysis per architecture, not per user per day)
- Free tier drives top-of-funnel; enterprise tier captures high-value accounts
- Credits carry over (no monthly reset anxiety) — customers buy when they need

---

## Tiers

### FREE — €0/month

For: Individual engineers evaluating Lens. No credit card required.

Includes:
- 1 analysis per month
- IAM role input only
- Up to 10 AWS services discovered
- Hetzner as target cloud only
- Basic report: score + service table
- No AI executive summary
- No PDF export
- No team access
- Reports retained for 30 days

Purpose: Remove all friction from first use. The report itself is the
sales motion — seeing your own infrastructure mapped against Hetzner
is more convincing than any marketing copy.

---

### STARTER — €49/month (billed annually: €39/month)

For: Startups and engineering teams actively evaluating a migration.

Includes everything in Free, plus:
- 5 analyses/month (extra credits: €9 each)
- All input methods: IAM role, Terraform upload, Helm upload
- All discovered AWS services (full 19-service MVP)
- Hetzner + 1 additional sovereign cloud (OVHcloud or Scaleway)
- AI executive summary on each report
- PDF export
- Reports retained for 1 year
- 2 team seats (share reports, not analysis runs)
- Email support

Who buys this:
A 10–30 person startup with AWS bills starting to hurt. They want a
clear answer before spending engineering time scoping a migration.

---

### GROWTH — €149/month (billed annually: €119/month)

For: Scale-ups running multiple products or environments on AWS.

Includes everything in Starter, plus:
- 20 analyses/month (extra credits: €7 each)
- All 6 sovereign clouds (Hetzner, OVHcloud, Scaleway, AWS EU Sovereign,
  Google Sovereign, Azure Sovereign)
- Side-by-side multi-cloud comparison report
- Full AI layer: executive summary + per-service gap explanations +
  alternatives + priority-ordered migration plan
- Rule engine violations panel (SaaS lock-in, structural risks)
- Drift detection: re-run same account monthly, flag new services added
  since last analysis
- 10 team seats
- Slack/webhook notifications for drift alerts
- Priority email support (24h response)

Who buys this:
A 50–200 person company with multiple AWS accounts, a CTO who has been
told to reduce cloud spend or improve data sovereignty compliance, and
an engineering team that needs a structured plan — not just a gut feeling.

---

### ENTERPRISE — Custom (starting ~€500/month)

For: Companies with complex AWS footprints, compliance requirements,
or internal security constraints that prevent sharing an IAM role.

Includes everything in Growth, plus:
- Unlimited analyses
- Multi-account AWS discovery (scan multiple AWS accounts in one report)
- CLI Export mode: customer runs the scanner locally, uploads results —
  no IAM role granted to Noblinks
- Custom catalog entries: add internal SaaS tools, proprietary services,
  or target clouds not in the standard catalog
- Private deployment option (run Lens in customer's own infrastructure)
- SSO / SAML authentication
- Audit log: full record of who ran what analysis and when
- SLA: 99.9% uptime, dedicated support channel
- Quarterly catalog review: Noblinks team updates catalog entries for
  new Hetzner/OVHcloud services relevant to the account
- Unlimited team seats
- Custom contract + DPA (Data Processing Agreement for GDPR)

Who buys this:
A financial services or healthcare company in Germany or the Netherlands
that has been audited and needs documented evidence that their migration
plan is based on structured, reproducible analysis — not an AI chatbot.

