## Freemium Conversion Path

Free → Starter trigger: user has run 1 free analysis and wants to:
  - Try a different input method (Terraform)
  - Compare against OVHcloud, not just Hetzner
  - Get the AI executive summary (the most visible locked feature)
  - Share the report with their team

Starter → Growth trigger: user has a multi-environment AWS setup
(dev/staging/prod) and needs 3+ analyses. Or they want multi-cloud
comparison to inform which EU sovereign cloud to choose.

Growth → Enterprise trigger: procurement, legal, or security team
gets involved. They need a DPA, audit logs, no IAM role sharing,
or a custom target cloud.

---

## What NOT to Do

- Do not price per seat — this is not a daily-use tool like Jira.
  Seats add friction without matching how customers think about value.
- Do not price purely per-report — it trains customers to treat it as
  a one-off tool and kills recurring revenue.
- Do not offer a free trial of paid tiers — the free tier is the trial.
  It produces a real report with real data. That is better than any trial.
- Do not discount heavily for startup programs — the value signal is high
  even for startups. Offer a startup application process with a fixed 50%
  discount for verified early-stage companies, but keep list price firm.

---

## Launch Strategy

Phase 1 (now):    Free + Starter only. Validate willingness to pay.
Phase 2 (3–6mo):  Add Growth when drift detection is built.
Phase 3 (6–12mo): Enterprise when multi-account + SSO + CLI export are ready.

Do not launch all tiers at once. The free + one paid tier model
reduces decision paralysis and focuses the team on one conversion goal.
